{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos723.erdos_723 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos723.erdos_723.","id":"vf_395aa61e9d6c10d8","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #723 [status: falsifiable; formalized: yes]. If there is a finite projective plane of order $n$ then must $n$ be a prime power?\n\nA finite projective plane of order $n$ is a collection of subsets of $\\{1,\\ldots,n^2+n+1\\}$ of size $n+1$ such that every pair of elements is contained in exactly one set. Current best: This conjecture has been proved for $n\\leq 11$, but it is open whether there exists a projective plane of order $12$. Prize: no. Tags: combinatorics.","id":"vf_9d11b2829a90d809","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/723.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_395aa61e9d6c10d8","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:723","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_395aa61e9d6c10d8","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"vf_9d11b2829a90d809","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_9d11b2829a90d809","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:723","trust":"signed"}],"external_references":[],"formal_conjectures_activity":null,"frontier_id":"vfr_0a25edabc16db143","frontier_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704b